    "## 12. Relationship Between Machining Parameters and Variance of Surface Roughness\n",
    "\n",
    "To better understand the source of heteroscedasticity in the machining process, this section examines whether the variability in surface roughness depends on the full set of machining parameters: depth of cut (ap), cutting speed (vc), and feed rate (f). Rather than assuming a single driver of variance, we evaluate whether multiple factors contribute to changes in dispersion.\n"
   ]
