   "source": [
    "### 12.1 Methodology: Residual-Based Variance Modeling\n",
    "\n",
    "Variance is assessed indirectly using the absolute values of normalized residuals from the fitted mixed-effects model. These values act as a proxy for local variability in surface roughness:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "|e_i| \\approx \\text{local variability of Ra}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "To identify potential sources of heteroscedasticity, regression models are fitted using each machining parameter individually and jointly."
