   "source": [
    "### 13.1 Rationale for the Final Approach\n",
    "\n",
    "Initial diagnostic checks (residual plots and variance regression analyses) showed clear evidence of heteroscedasticity:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Residual variance increases with feed rate\n",
    "- Cutting speed (vc = 390) also shows elevated variability\n",
    "- Depth of cut has a weaker and less consistent effect\n",
    "\n",
    "A standard homoscedastic mixed model would therefore underestimate variability at higher factor levels and potentially inflate Type I error rates."
   ]
  },
