   "source": [
    "### 13.2 Final Variance Structure\n",
    "\n",
    "To account for non-constant variance, a heteroscedastic mixed-effects model is specified using a variance function that allows different residual variances across feed rate levels:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\mathrm{Var}(\\varepsilon_{ijkl}) = \\sigma^2 \\cdot f^{2\\delta}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "This structure allows the error variance to differ depending on the level of feed rate, capturing the dominant source of heteroscedasticity identified in the data."
   ]
  },
