   "source": [
    "### 13.3 Final Model Specification\n",
    "\n",
    "The final model is a linear mixed-effects model used to explain surface roughness (Ra) while accounting for both mean structure and changing variability.\n",
    "\n",
    "- Fixed effects: ap, vc, f and selected interactions  \n",
    "- Random effects: Run (to capture run-to-run variability)  \n",
    "- Heteroskedastic variance structure: variance increases with feed rate  \n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "y_{ijkl} = \\mu + A_i + B_j + C_k + (AB)_{ij} + (AC)_{ik} + (BC)_{jk} + b_l + \\varepsilon_{ijkl}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "b_l \\sim N(0, \\sigma^2_{Run})\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "and the residual variance is modeled as a function of feed rate rather than as separate variance estimates for each level:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\mathrm{Var}(\\varepsilon_{ijkl}) = \\sigma^2 \\cdot f^{2\\delta}\n",
    "$$"
   ]
