    "### 14.2 Variance Structure and Model Adequacy\n",
    "\n",
    "Diagnostic analysis revealed that the assumption of constant variance was violated, with variability increasing across machining conditions—particularly with higher feed rates.\n",
    "\n",
    "This was addressed using a heteroscedastic mixed-effects model, allowing residual variance to vary by feed rate. This adjustment:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Improved model fit (lower AIC)\n",
    "- Produced more reliable standard errors\n",
    "- Reduced bias in statistical inference"
